</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C328653BB44BFFE0A9B2D4DFFEF6A235" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B8D36B0B44BFFE0A9B2D4DFFEF6A235" blockId="21.[151,1437,694,1726]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="B946EAA2B44BFFE0A9B2D4DFFEA4A1D8" bold="true" box="[201,336,1487,1511]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Etymology.</emphasis>
The genus name is formed by combining the Sanskrit word Skanda (to jump) + 
<taxonomicName id="4C324D33B44BFFE0AD97D4DEFAB6A1D9" box="[1260,1346,1486,1510]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Agallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Agallia</taxonomicName>
, gender feminine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C328653BB44BFFE0A9B2D707FE7DA281" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8D36B0B44BFFE0A9B2D707FE7DA281" blockId="21.[151,1437,694,1726]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="B946EAA2B44BFFE0A9B2D707FEC9A210" bold="true" box="[201,317,1559,1583]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C324D33B44BFFE0A832D706FE29A211" box="[329,477,1558,1582]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Skandagallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B946EAA2B44BFFE0A832D706FE29A211" box="[329,477,1558,1582]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Skandagallia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C324D33B44BFFE0AB65D706FD7EA211" box="[542,650,1558,1582]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Sungallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B946EAA2B44BFFE0AB65D706FD7EA211" box="[542,650,1558,1582]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Sungallia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27557D9B44BFFE0ABEED707FCF0A210" box="[661,772,1559,1583]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B946EAA2B44BFFE0ABEED707FCF0A210" bold="true" box="[661,772,1559,1583]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">gen. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(see below) are brachypterous genera as in the case of 
<taxonomicName id="4C324D33B44BFFE0A9ECD72BFEAAA26D" authority="Distant" authorityName="Distant" box="[151,350,1594,1619]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Gunhilda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B946EAA2B44BFFE0A9ECD72BFEF5A26C" box="[151,257,1595,1619]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Gunhilda</emphasis>
Distant
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<emphasis id="B946EAA2B44BFFE0A8E5D72BFDD0A26C" box="[414,548,1595,1619]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Nandigallia</emphasis>
Viraktamath wherein both brachypterous and mactopterous forms are found. 
<taxonomicName id="4C324D33B44BFFE0A9ECD74EFEDFA249" box="[151,299,1630,1654]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Skandagallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B946EAA2B44BFFE0A9ECD74EFEDFA249" box="[151,299,1630,1654]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Skandagallia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the other genera in having a posteriorly declivous male pygofer ending in an acute process as in the case of 
<taxonomicName id="4C324D33B44BFFE0A8CFD793FD9EA2A4" box="[436,618,1667,1691]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Anaceratagallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B946EAA2B44BFFE0A8CFD793FD9EA2A4" box="[436,618,1667,1691]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Anaceratagallia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C324D33B44BFFE0AA58D793FC2DA2A4" box="[803,985,1667,1691]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Anaceratagallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B946EAA2B44BFFE0AA58D793FC2DA2A4" box="[803,985,1667,1691]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Anaceratagallia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the structure of the style, connective and subgenital plates.
</paragraph>
